&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 4 Team Leader, LTHT Resourcing &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Leeds Teaching Hospitals is one of the largest teaching hospitals in the UK and employs over 16,000 staff and we would like to offer you the opportunity to join our busy resourcing team.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Responsible for supervising a small team of Resourcing Officers and Resourcing Assistants, you will be the lead for the recruitment and employment of staff in a number of different areas across the Trust. You will support the team in providing advice regarding recruitment and terms and conditions eg: starting salary, acting up, eligibility to work in the UK, mandatory pre-employment checks and other employment related matters.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Liaison with external agencies and internal customers is also a key part of the role, to deliver a high quality, customer focussed service to the organisation. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Knowledge of NHS Terms and Conditions of Service is essential, as well as an understanding of good practice and legal requirements relating to recruitment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent organisational and interpersonal skills are required together with the ability to work well under pressure whilst maintaining attention to detail. Working well as part of a team in addition to being able to use personal initiative is essential, as is a clear commitment to providing a high standard of customer service. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Excellent computer/keyboard skills and previous office experience are also essential. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a need for flexibility around working hours to meet fluctuating demands in the service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like any futher information about the role, please contact Joe Eastell, Senior Team Leader on 0113 206 6495 or e-mail &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;joe.eastell@nhs.net &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
